  <description><![CDATA[<p>If you can’t sit still (or if that’s all you want to do) then the Refuge des Aiglons is the place for you with a range of facilities, delicious food and a great location.</p>
<h2>Summer fun and facilities</h2>
<p>Water babies will love the outdoor swimming pool for cooling off during those balmy summer days, its surrounded by sun loungers so book worms can get stuck into a good book, or, simply relax and enjoy views of the surrounding Mont Blanc Massif. The spa and wellness facilities are great for cooler days with a steam room, sauna and whirlpool available to enjoy. For a bit of friendly competition, you’ll find a small games room with table football, board games, books and a few other games to get stuck into. Or, those that love riddles should try out the hotels own escape game – its free to try and is fun for all the family.</p>
<h2>A great location for those discovering Chamonix</h2>
<p>For those wanting to get out and about, you’re just 200 metres from the centre of Chamonix, here you’ll find a vibrant mountain town where adventure is a way of life. And you can’t visit Chamonix without a trip in Europe’s steepest cable car, the Aiguille du Midi, which is just around the corner from the hotel. You’re also just across the road from the bus station meaning you can connect to other neighbouring towns and villages, which is particularly good for those wanting to get out and explore the local walking trails. After exploring, head back to the hotel to the large outdoor terrace for a well-deserved aperitif from the hotel bar and on warmer summer evenings dinner can also be enjoyed on the terrace.</p>]]></description>
