  <roomsDescription><![CDATA[<p><strong>Standard valley view rooms</strong> are about 20m², sleep up to two people and can have a double bed or twin beds (please specify preference when booking). They also have a bath with shower head.</p>
<p><strong>Superior Mont Blanc view rooms</strong> are about 25m², sleep up to three people and can have a double bed or twin beds (please specify preference when booking, please note the third bed is a single sofa bed). These rooms have a balcony with a view of Mont Blanc.</p>
<p><strong>Junior suites</strong> are a lot more spacious at about 40m², sleep up to four people and the main bed can be made as a double bed or twin beds (please specify preference when booking. Please note that the extra bed is a double sofa bed). They also have a small seating area.</p>
<p><strong>Single rooms and interconnecting Rooms</strong> are available on request and at a supplement, please call to book.</p>
<p>Cots are available on request.</p>
<p><strong>All rooms have:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Tea &amp; coffee making facilities</li>
<li>Bathrobe &amp; slippers</li>
<li>Hairdryer</li>
<li>TV</li>
<li>Minibar</li>
<li>Safe</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>General information</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Check in: <strong>5pm</strong></li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Local fees and taxes</strong></p>
<p>Resort tax of approx. €2.30 per person, per day is payable locally (free for under 18's)</p>]]></roomsDescription>
